item.title: [SGF-221] Unable to register GemFire Async Event Listeners on SubRegions.
item.description:
The following snippet of Spring Data GemFire context configuration meta-data...

  <gfe:replicated-region id="Customers" persistent="false">
 
    <gfe:replicated-region name="Accounts" persistent="false">
 
      <gfe:async-event-queue name="QueueOne" maximum-queue-memory="50" parallel="true" dispatcher-threads="4" order-policy="KEY">
 
        <gfe:async-event-listener>
 
          <bean class="org.spring.data.gemfire.cache.asyncqueue.NoOpAsyncEventListener"/>
 
        </gfe:async-event-listener>
 
      </gfe:async-event-queue>
 
    </gfe:replicated-region>
 
  </gfe:replicated-region>

Throws the following Exception when the Spring container starts...

Exception in thread "main" org.springframework.beans.factory.BeanCreationException: Error creating bean with name '/Customers/Accounts/Orders/Items': Cannot resolve reference to bean '/Customers/Accounts/Orders' while setting bean property 'parent'; nested exception is org.springframework.beans.factory.BeanCreationException: Error creating bean with name '/Customers/Accounts/Orders': Cannot resolve reference to bean '/Customers/Accounts' while setting bean property 'parent'; nested exception is org.springframework.beans.factory.BeanCreationException: Error creating bean with name '/Customers/Accounts': Error setting property values; nested exception is org.springframework.beans.NotWritablePropertyException: Invalid property 'asyncEventQueues' of bean class [org.springframework.data.gemfire.SubRegionFactoryBean]: Bean property 'asyncEventQueues' is not writable or has an invalid setter method.
